\f0\fs56 \cf2 Directions\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\fs48 \cf3 		Place vinegar and peppers in a blender; cover and puree. Add 2 cups sugar; blend well. Pour into a saucepan. Stir in the remaining sugar; bring to a boil. Strain mixture and return to pan. Stir in pectin and food coloring if desired. Return to a rolling boil over high heat. Boil for 2\
		minutes, stirring constantly.
\fs56 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs48 		Remove from the heat; skim off foam. Carefully ladle hot mixture into hot sterilized half-pint jars, leaving 1/4-in. headspace. Remove air\
		bubbles, wipe rims and adjust lids. Process for 5 minutes in a boiling-water canner.
\fs56 \
\ls2\ilvl0
\fs48 		Serve with cream cheese on crackers. \
\ls2\ilvl0
